{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2024-01-07","name":"Alexander Forbes","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Alexander Forbes","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Alexander"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"Forbes"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"gender":"Male","lifespan":"1256–1303","fullLifespan":"1256–1303","birthDate":"+1256","birthPlace":{"address":"Forbes, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","geo":{"latitude":57.245,"longitude":-2.7262,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1303","deathPlace":{"address":"Morayshire, Scotland","geo":{"latitude":57.4167,"longitude":-3.25,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"burialDate":"+1303","burialPlace":{"address":"Morayshire, Scotland","geo":{"latitude":57.41667,"longitude":-3.25,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nALEXANDER FORBES, who was a man of great magnanimity and courage, and a true lover of his country. He was captain and governour of the castle of Urquhart, which he gallantly defended against king Edward I. of England,* to the very last extremity, and on no terms could be prevailed on to surrender. In the end the castle was taken by storm, and the whole garrison, with himself and all his sons, were put to the sword, anno 1303; but happily his lady being with child was delivered of a son, who succeeded him, and carried on the line of this family.","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1256","date":"1256","place":"Forbes, Aberdeenshire, Scotland"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1272","date":"1272","place":"Somme, Picardie, France","age":"16","id":"G3Z1-7LQ"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1286","date":"1286","place":"Forbes, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","age":"30","id":"GSZH-QHQ"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1300","date":"1300","place":"Scotland","age":"44","id":"2ZSC-VT5"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1303","date":"1303","place":"Morayshire, Scotlan